---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Local Content Strategy: Create Pages That Rank Locally | visibilite-locale.online"
  description="Create content optimized for local search. Service pages, geo-targeted blog posts, and local editorial strategy."
  lang="en"
  ogImage="/images/guide/en-local-content.webp"

>
  <section class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
      <nav class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <a href="/en/" class="hover:text-blue-600">Home</a> &rsaquo;
        <a href="/en/guide-seo-local" class="hover:text-blue-600">Local SEO Guide</a> &rsaquo;
        <span class="text-gray-900">Local Content</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">Local Content and Geo-Targeted Pages</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Create pages and articles targeting your geographic area to capture local traffic.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <!-- Image hero -->
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pt-8">
    <img
      src="/images/guide/en-local-content.webp"
      alt=""
      class="w-full rounded-xl object-cover shadow-sm"
      loading="eager"
      width="1200"
      height="400"
      style="max-height:320px"
      onerror="this.style.display='none'"
    />
  </div>


  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 prose">
      <h2>Why create local content</h2>
      <p>
        Geo-targeted content helps Google understand which areas you serve. Pages optimized for specific cities or neighborhoods capture qualified local traffic.
      </p>

      <h2>Types of local pages</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Service pages by city</strong>: "Plumber in Chicago", "Dentist in Houston"</li>
        <li><strong>Service area pages</strong>: cover the cities and neighborhoods you serve</li>
        <li><strong>Local blog posts</strong>: local events, neighborhood guides, industry news in your area</li>
        <li><strong>Local team pages</strong>: present team members by location</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Optimizing local content</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Include the city name in the title, meta description, and H1</li>
        <li>Mention local landmarks (neighborhoods, monuments, well-known streets)</li>
        <li>Add an embedded Google Maps widget</li>
        <li>Include testimonials from local customers</li>
        <li>Add LocalBusiness schema markup</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Avoiding duplicate content</h2>
      <p>
        Don't create nearly identical pages by just changing the city name. Each local page should contain unique, relevant content for the targeted area.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Related articles</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 text-blue-700">
          <li><a href="/en/blog/en-mots-cles-locaux/">How to Find the Right Keywords for Local SEO</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
